<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="50" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Peterson</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-25"><hi rend="italic">February 25,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Obtain further deposition from Cranstoun as to when he arrived in United
                            States, when and where he was naturalized, and as to whether he took up
                            his residence in Hawaii intending to abide there permanently or
                            indefinitely.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. GRESHAM.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>